\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 50.    Eremopyrum}        (Ledeb.)Jaub.& Spach
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By A. Melderis. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Annuals. Leaves flat; ligule short. Inflorescence a dense, compressed spike. Spikelets solitary at each node of the rhachis, arranged alternately and pectinately, sessile, with 3-6 florets, strongly compressed laterally; rhachilla disarticulating above the glumes and below the florets. Glumes equal, coriaceous, becoming very hard at maturity, with a prominent keel, connate at the base, unawned or shortly awned. Lemma coriaceous, 5-veined, keeled, acute or awned. Palea shorter than the lemma, membranous, 2-keeled, ciliate on the keels in the upper part.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   Literature: N. L. Bor in K. H. Rechinger,{\i  Flora Iranica}{\b  70}: 185-191. Graz. 1970.
